OL,3,CDriver dumps bags of rubbish 'because
OL,4,Ctip was closed'
OL,6,F"When we drive to work we see
OL,7,Fmattresses on our roads and things
OL,8,Flike that. Fly-tipping is a problem
OL,9,Fhere, but this is the first time I've
OL,10,Fseen something like this. It was so
OL,11,Fblatant - it's just ridiculous."
OL,12,FBirmingham City Council has recently
OL,13,Fsecured almost #50,000 to combat the
OL,14,Ffly-tipping 'blight' across the city.
OL,15,FThe money comes from a government
OL,16,Fgrant aimed at setting up CCTV
OL,17,Fnetworks to catch fly-tippers in the
OL,18,Fact and increase the levels of
OL,19,Fprosecution.JCurrent rules mean a
OL,20,Ffixed penalty notice (FPN) of #150 is
OL,21,Fgiven to those caught littering, which
OL,22,Ffor fly-tipping can increase to
OL,23,F#50,000 and potentially imprisonment
OL,24,Fif someone refuses to pay.
